    "content": "**Yes, this works.** \n\n\"Traditional metaphysics\" is the author's own term, reads naturally in English, and is immediately understood by any philosophical reader. The TN glossing it as \"pre-nihilist\" specifies the structural dividing line without burdening the main text. And it pairs cleanly with \"post-metaphysics\" -- the reader sees traditional/post as the before/after of the same crisis.\n\nMy one concern about \"pre-critical\" importing too much Kantian framing is resolved by this solution: the TN says \"pre-nihilist,\" which names the author's actual dividing line (nihilism, not Kant's critical turn). Readers who know Kant will see the parallel on their own; the translation does not force it.\n\nGood compromise.\n"
